ng unit determines the grade of a second RSSI. The second presumed lined calculating unit calculates the range of the object from a second node based on the grade of the second RSSI. The presumed location calculation unit calculates two presumed locations. The final location calculation unit determines one of the two presumed locations to be the final location of the object.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>